    if (right - left > k) {
        set.remove(nums[left]);
        left++;
    }
If the window size exceeds k, we slide it forward by:

Removing nums[left] from the set

Moving the left pointer ahead

âš ï¸ Ensures that the window size is at most k

java
Copy
Edit
    if (set.contains(nums[right])) {
        return true;
    }
If the current element already exists in the window, return true â€” we found a duplicate within k distance.

java
Copy
Edit
    set.add(nums[right]);
Add the current element to the set (now part of the sliding window)

ğŸ§  Example:
java
