Step by step:

right	left	nums[right]	set	contains duplicate?	window size	Action
0	0	1	{1}	No	1	Add 1
1	0	2	{1,2}	No	2	Add 2
2	0	3	{1,2,3}	No	3	Add 3
3	0	1	{1,2,3}	âœ… Yes	4 â†’ shrink	Return true

â±ï¸ Time Complexity:
O(n) â€“ each element is added and removed from the HashSet at most once.

ğŸ—ƒï¸ Space Complexity:
O(min(n, k)) â€“ at most k elements in the set at any time.

âœ… When to Use:
Use this technique when you're asked to find duplicates within a certain distance (k) in a list. Itâ€™s an optimized way to avoid nested loops.

Let me know if you want to see the brute force or optimized using HashMap as well.

class Solution {
    public boolean containsNearbyDuplicate(int[] nums, int k) {
        Set<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();
        int left = 0;
        for(int right = 0;right<nums.length;right++){
            if(right-left>k){
                set.remove(nums[left]);
                left++;
            }
            if(set.contains(nums[right])){
                return true;
            }
            set.add(nums[right]);
        }
        return false;
    }
}
